        First, let's start with adding new terrain.
      </TouchText>
    </Step>
    <Step>
      <Comment>Add new terrain.</Comment>
      <DisplayMode>NonModal</DisplayMode>
      <Exclusion>None</Exclusion>
      <TargetModeGamepad>GamepadTerrainPaint</TargetModeGamepad>
      <TargetModeMouse>MouseTerrainPaint</TargetModeMouse>
      <TargetModeTouch>TouchTerrainPaint</TargetModeTouch>
      <GoalText>Painting terrain (Step 1/3)</GoalText>
      <GamepadText>Press &lt;A&gt; to paint, &lt;righttrigger&gt; to add new ground and &lt;lefttrigger&gt; to delete.</GamepadText>
      <MouseText>
        Use the left mouse button &lt;leftmouse&gt; to paint and the right mouse button &lt;rightmouse&gt; to delete.
        You can also add terrain by painting beyond the edge of the existing world.
      </MouseText>
      <TouchText>
        Use your finger to paint.  Tap on the eraser to delete.
        You can also add terrain by painting beyond the edge of the existing world.
      </TouchText>
      <CompletionTest Name="Terra" Args="add paint" />
    </Step>
    <Step>
      <Comment>Painting.</Comment>
      <DisplayMode>NonModal</DisplayMode>
      <Exclusion>None</Exclusion>
      <TargetModeGamepad>GamepadTerrainPaint</TargetModeGamepad>
